main event: A military personnel sighted a round, blue-green object the size of a dime at Whidbey NAS, Washington, on 17 Feb 1959.
interesting points: The sighting lasted approximately 1 minute with the object being observed for 1-6 seconds., The reported object appeared as a round, blue-green object which was later concluded to possibly be a balloon., There were reliable military witnesses involved in the sighting., The object disappeared on the horizon moving straight from northwest to southeast., Weather conditions at the time included scattered clouds and a cirrus overcast at 14,000 feet.
sighted object: round, blue-green object the size of a dime
witness description: reliable military personnel from Whidbey NAS
